# Agent config is per-developer and stays out — except `skills/`, which is project knowledge (how to
# drive this program, what its gotchas are) rather than anyone's local setup. Negating a whole
# ignored directory doesn't work, so the contents are ignored and skills/ is let back in.
# `worktrees/` in particular must never be tracked: it holds nested git checkouts.
**/.claude/*
!**/.claude/skills/
